$lang['Hexadecimal is a way of representing binary data in human-readable form. It was developed in the 19th century to allow computers to store large amounts of information.'] = 'Heksadesimal minangka cara makili data biner ing wangun sing bisa diwaca manungsa. Iki dikembangake ing abad kaping 19 kanggo ngidini komputer nyimpen informasi sing akeh.';
$lang['You can use hexadecimal to convert between decimal and binary values. For example, converting 10011011001010 into hexadecimal would result in 0x4F. This means that the value 4F represents the binary number 100110110010110.'] = 'Sampeyan bisa nggunakake heksadesimal kanggo ngowahi antarane nilai desimal lan binar. Contone, ngowahi 10011011001010 dadi heksadesimal bakal ngasilake 0x4F. Iki tegese nilai 4F nuduhake angka biner 100110110010110.';
$lang['In mathematics and computer science, hexadecimal (also base 16, or hex) is a positional numeral system with a radix, or base, of 16. It uses sixteen distinct symbols, most often the symbols 0–9 to represent values zero to nine, and A, B, C, D, E, F (or alternatively a–f) to represent values ten to fifteen. For example, the hexadecimal number 2AF3 is equal, in decimal, to (2 × 163) + (10 × 162) + (15 × 161) + (3 × 160) , or 10,995.'] = 'Ing matématika lan èlmu komputer, heksadesimal (uga basis 16, utawa hex) minangka sistem angka posisional kanthi radix, utawa basis, saka 16. Iki nggunakake enem welas simbol sing béda-béda, paling asring simbol 0-9 kanggo makili angka nol nganti sangang, lan A, B, C, D, E, F (utawa alternatif a–f) kanggo makili nilai sepuluh nganti limalas. Contone, nomer heksadesimal 2AF3 padha, ing desimal, kanggo (2 × 163) + (10 × 162) + (15 × 161) + (3 × 160) , utawa 10.995.';
$lang['Each hexadecimal digit represents four binary digits (bits) (also called a "nibble"), and the primary use of hexadecimal notation is as a human-friendly representation of binary coded values in computing and digital electronics. For example, byte values can range from 0 to 255 (decimal) but may be more conveniently represented as two hexadecimal digits in the range 00 through FF. Hexadecimal is also commonly used to represent computer memory addresses.'] = 'Saben digit heksadesimal nggambarake papat digit biner (bit) (uga disebut &quot;nibble&quot;), lan panggunaan utama notasi heksadesimal minangka representasi nilai-nilai kode biner sing ramah manungsa ing komputasi lan elektronik digital. Contone, nilai byte bisa saka 0 nganti 255 (desimal) nanging luwih gampang dituduhake minangka rong digit heksadesimal ing kisaran 00 nganti FF. Heksadesimal uga umum digunakake kanggo makili alamat memori komputer.';
$lang['Hex is an abbreviation of Hexadecimal, which is based on a base -16 structure and is used for simplifying how instructions to computers are represented. This 16 symbols number system was developed as a means of inhibiting an 8-bit binary number, so data can be encoded into computers effortlessly. It can be imprinted and typed using two different hex digits with each hex digit demonstrating a nibble or perhaps a 4-bits format.'] = 'Hex minangka singkatan saka Hexadecimal, sing adhedhasar struktur basis -16 lan digunakake kanggo nyederhanakake carane instruksi kanggo komputer dituduhake. Sistem angka 16 simbol iki dikembangake minangka sarana kanggo nyegah angka biner 8-bit, saengga data bisa dikodekake menyang komputer kanthi gampang. Bisa dicithak lan diketik nggunakake rong digit hex beda karo saben digit hex nuduhake nibble utawa format 4-bit.';
$lang['This number system uses 16 symbols that are represented in a range from 0-9 or A-F. The 0–9 represent numbers up to nine whereas A-F is represented by the numeric 10–15. As compared to the other three types of number systems, the hexadecimal numeral system is considered to be the most effective one.'] = 'Sistem nomer iki nggunakake 16 simbol sing dituduhake ing sawetara saka 0-9 utawa AF. Angka 0–9 nuduhake angka nganti sangang, dene AF diwakili angka 10–15. Dibandhingake karo telung jinis sistem nomer liyane, sistem angka heksadesimal dianggep paling efektif.';
